WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:07.442
Previously on
"Just Add Magic"...

00:07.529 --> 00:09.705
Pluots are dumb.

00:09.792 --> 00:11.881
And I'm sick of all of you.

00:11.968 --> 00:13.839
We're gonna
bring this place back
the old fashioned way.

00:13.926 --> 00:16.668
No more spells, Mama P.
No magic.

00:16.755 --> 00:19.497
And just to be clear,
we're not friends.

00:19.584 --> 00:21.369
Hannah:
She's playing in public.

00:21.456 --> 00:23.023
That means
her curse broke, too.

00:23.110 --> 00:24.502
Kelly:
Grandma lied to me.

00:24.589 --> 00:25.982
She said that Chuck
stole her seed.

00:26.069 --> 00:27.897
Why would Grandma Becky lie?

00:27.984 --> 00:30.117
You are the protectors
of the book.

00:30.204 --> 00:31.118
It is in danger.

00:31.205 --> 00:32.467
[gasping]

00:32.554 --> 00:34.077
Look at these new symbols.

00:34.164 --> 00:35.252
What do you think
it means?

00:41.780 --> 00:44.696
♪♪

00:46.000 --> 00:52.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:53.096 --> 00:55.185
[chatter]

01:04.325 --> 01:05.239
Charles.

01:09.460 --> 01:11.462
It's been a while.

01:11.549 --> 01:12.507
Happy to see me?

01:12.594 --> 01:14.248
I know what you're up to.

01:14.335 --> 01:17.599
So?
You can't stop me.

01:17.686 --> 01:18.687
Not again.

01:18.774 --> 01:21.385
This is a second chance.

01:21.472 --> 01:23.083
Don't make
the same mistakes.

01:23.170 --> 01:26.956
The only mistake I made
was not finishing the job.

01:27.043 --> 01:28.000
Give it to me.

01:28.088 --> 01:30.177
You know I can't.

01:30.264 --> 01:31.395
But this is
an opportunity--

01:31.482 --> 01:35.530
Don't bother.
I will get it back.

01:35.617 --> 01:36.574
No matter what it takes.

01:42.058 --> 01:44.843
I haven't eaten
in 50 years.

01:44.930 --> 01:46.715
I was hoping for
a burger and shake.

01:46.802 --> 01:49.196
Please,
don't make me use this.

01:49.283 --> 01:51.502
That's your bluff.

01:51.589 --> 01:53.243
We both know how much
that's going to hurt you.

01:53.330 --> 01:56.116
A sacrifice
I'm willing to make.

01:56.203 --> 01:57.987
Charles, stop this.
Now.

01:58.074 --> 01:59.989
Not until I get
what I want.

02:00.076 --> 02:01.121
Then I'm sorry.

02:03.384 --> 02:04.298
Don't!

02:15.222 --> 02:16.353
Where am I?

02:20.575 --> 02:23.621
Hey, ma'am,
are you okay?

02:24.666 --> 02:26.102
Be safe.

02:28.365 --> 02:31.238
♪♪

02:34.197 --> 02:35.764
If these symbols
are a language,

02:35.851 --> 02:37.548
it's definitely not one
the internet knows.

02:37.635 --> 02:40.812
Maybe someone just got bored
and doodled in the margins.

02:40.899 --> 02:42.901
That could be
a spaceship.

02:42.988 --> 02:45.208
Or a puppy.
No, a spaceship.

02:45.295 --> 02:46.949
Maybe we're
going about this
the wrong way.

02:47.036 --> 02:49.691
If the book has secrets,
then we should talk to

02:49.778 --> 02:51.693
the one who knows it
better than we ever could.

02:51.780 --> 02:53.260
You're talking about
the traveler.

02:53.347 --> 02:56.437
The traveler for doodles
in the margin?

02:56.524 --> 02:58.178
Yeah, I don't think we're
supposed to call her

02:58.265 --> 03:00.049
every time we have
a question.

03:00.136 --> 03:01.442
Also, I don't think
she has a phone.

03:01.529 --> 03:03.618
[chuckles]
But she can help us,

03:03.705 --> 03:05.446
we just have to
find her.

03:05.533 --> 03:07.665
Oh, no,
are we gonna have to
face our fears again?

03:07.752 --> 03:09.363
Okay,
facing fears again,

03:09.450 --> 03:10.886
and that's my cue
to exit.

03:10.973 --> 03:13.018
I'm off to Miss Silvers'
for my piano lesson.

03:13.105 --> 03:14.629
- Have fun.
- Bye.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.935
I have a recipe
that shows me where

03:17.022 --> 03:18.676
the traveler will appear.

03:18.763 --> 03:20.678
I've used it before
to track her down.

03:20.765 --> 03:22.027
Great.
Let's get cooking.

03:22.114 --> 03:24.856
No. The traveler
gave this to me.

03:24.943 --> 03:26.945
I can only cook this
on my own.

03:27.032 --> 03:29.339
Really?
Because it feels like
we should do it together.

03:29.426 --> 03:31.646
It's fine.
Don't worry.

03:31.733 --> 03:34.039
Why don't you go have fun?
It's summer, you know.

03:34.126 --> 03:35.911
I keep trying to tell her.

03:35.998 --> 03:37.304
Come on, Kelly,
the symbols might
make more sense

03:37.391 --> 03:39.044
if we took
an ice cream break.

03:39.131 --> 03:42.570
Okay, maybe you're right.
Let's clear our heads.

03:46.791 --> 03:49.446
Grandma.

03:49.533 --> 03:51.840
You'll let me know
what the traveler says,
right?

03:51.927 --> 03:54.190
Of course.
Why would you even ask?

03:54.277 --> 03:56.932
No reason,
I just wanted to make sure
that you wouldn't forget

03:57.019 --> 03:58.412
to tell me about
something important.

03:58.499 --> 04:00.414
I won't forget.

04:00.501 --> 04:02.024
Go enjoy your day.

04:08.248 --> 04:10.424
Oh, hey, Mom.
Terri just got
some great news.

04:10.511 --> 04:12.208
Well, it's news.

04:12.295 --> 04:13.688
Remember how I
collected signatures

04:13.775 --> 04:15.298
after Buddy got hurt
skateboarding?

04:15.385 --> 04:17.909
Of course.
Saw the new speed bump.
Nice job.

04:17.995 --> 04:21.130
Someone at City Hall
noticed my activist spirit,

04:21.216 --> 04:23.785
- and decided to--
- They offered her a job
as the Mayor's aid.

04:23.872 --> 04:26.527
Oh, that's great.
Congratulations.

04:26.614 --> 04:29.094
Although, to be honest,
I didn't vote for her.

04:29.181 --> 04:30.661
[chuckling]

04:34.056 --> 04:35.318
Ambitious.

04:35.405 --> 04:36.972
I thought we agreed
on $7.50?

04:37.059 --> 04:38.495
[scoffs]
Who cares.

04:38.582 --> 04:40.802
The price doesn't matter
if nobody's buying.

04:40.889 --> 04:42.151
Well, they'll come
eventually.

04:42.238 --> 04:43.283
I don't know,
Mama P.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.197
Saffron Falls
holds a grudge.

04:45.285 --> 04:46.329
I'm heading to the park

04:46.416 --> 04:47.852
to try and make
some actual money.

04:47.939 --> 04:49.941
[chuckles]
Go get 'em.

04:50.028 --> 04:53.249
You just need one person to
take a bite of your chilled
ahi-mahi sandwich,

04:53.336 --> 04:54.990
and you'll be
raking in the cash.

04:55.077 --> 04:56.078
Let's hope you're right.

04:57.514 --> 04:59.951
Curling on your arpeggio
still needs work.

05:00.038 --> 05:02.606
[sighs]
There's so much
to remember.

05:02.693 --> 05:03.868
How do you
keep track of it all?

05:03.955 --> 05:07.219
Well, endless years
of practice.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.221
- Can I ask you a question?
- Mm-hm.

05:09.309 --> 05:11.528
Did you really play
at Carnegie Hall?

05:11.615 --> 05:12.703
I did.

05:15.053 --> 05:16.446
What was it like?

05:16.533 --> 05:18.709
Electrifying.
And terrifying.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.189
You were scared?

05:20.276 --> 05:23.323
Well, of course.
That is why you practice.

05:23.410 --> 05:25.150
So your body
can take over

05:25.237 --> 05:27.631
until the music
fills the room.

05:27.718 --> 05:30.286
The fear melts,

05:30.373 --> 05:32.506
and all that's left is joy.

05:32.593 --> 05:34.899
That sounds amazing.

05:34.986 --> 05:37.946
So, why haven't you
performed again?

05:38.033 --> 05:39.643
Your curse is broken.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.732
No one wants to
hear me play.

05:41.819 --> 05:43.343
I've been gone
for too long.

05:43.430 --> 05:45.823
That's ridiculous.
You're an excellent pianist.

05:45.910 --> 05:49.653
It doesn't matter.
The music world has
a short memory.

05:52.874 --> 05:55.964
Miss Silvers is a prodigy.
She should be playing again.

05:56.051 --> 05:58.053
She just needs someone
to give her a chance.

05:58.140 --> 06:00.185
Or a new
personality.

06:00.272 --> 06:02.449
What?
She's a little grumpy.

06:02.536 --> 06:03.972
Jake.
What's wrong?

06:04.059 --> 06:05.408
My fridge went out.

06:05.495 --> 06:07.454
That seems bad when
you deliver fish.

06:07.541 --> 06:10.021
Across town.
In summer.

06:10.108 --> 06:11.675
Tell me about it.

06:11.762 --> 06:13.938
- Oh, gross!
- Oh, I'm gonna be sick.

06:14.025 --> 06:16.027
A whole day's worth of sales
down the drain,

06:16.114 --> 06:17.681
not to mention
the cash I burned
on ingredients.

06:17.768 --> 06:19.161
That's terrible.

06:19.248 --> 06:21.119
It's always something
with this pile of junk.

06:21.206 --> 06:22.643
The tires went flat,
the heater broke,

06:22.730 --> 06:24.862
and now this fridge.

06:24.949 --> 06:27.604
- I'm sorry, Jake.
- And that's not
the worst of it.

06:27.691 --> 06:29.084
I have an appointment
with Jess Montel

06:29.171 --> 06:30.912
to try my food tomorrow.

06:30.999 --> 06:33.218
- And she is...
- Property manager
at PPM.

06:33.305 --> 06:35.699
- And they are...
- Pluot Property Management.

06:35.786 --> 06:38.049
They run the big
office complex
by the park.

06:38.136 --> 06:39.486
That could be
your big break.

06:39.573 --> 06:41.183
Not with a fridge
full of spoiled fish.

06:41.270 --> 06:42.706
I can't take on
an account this big

06:42.793 --> 06:45.187
with this piece of junk
breaking down every minute.

06:45.274 --> 06:47.755
I give up!

06:47.842 --> 06:50.366
Jake.
What do you want us to do
with your food bike?

06:50.453 --> 06:52.716
Put it in a dumpster
for all I care.

06:53.500 --> 06:54.892
Poor Jake.

06:54.979 --> 06:56.981
It's not fair
this keeps happening
to him.

06:57.068 --> 07:00.420
I know. I wish
we could help him.

07:00.507 --> 07:03.858
- We could.
- No magic is gonna bring
that fish back.

07:03.945 --> 07:06.251
No, but it might be able to
bring Jake's business back.

07:06.338 --> 07:08.340
Come on.
It's not his fault.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.952
He's only in this mess
because Mama P
stole his other bike.

07:11.039 --> 07:12.344
True.

07:12.432 --> 07:13.824
And he's not
impressing anyone

07:13.911 --> 07:14.825
with his bike
like this.

07:14.912 --> 07:16.566
For real.

07:16.653 --> 07:18.133
Okay.
Let's do it.

07:19.613 --> 07:21.789
Maybe there's
a no rust recipe.

07:23.138 --> 07:24.966
"Chicken-N-Fixits."

07:25.053 --> 07:27.447
"When anything fails,
heat up your skillet,

07:27.534 --> 07:30.058
"see to the problem,
then you may fix it."

07:30.145 --> 07:32.713
So this'll let us see
what's wrong with Jake's bike?

07:32.800 --> 07:35.106
"Finish the job,
even magic abates,

07:35.193 --> 07:37.935
"but if left incomplete,
labor long with no breaks."

07:38.022 --> 07:39.720
That's ominous.

07:39.807 --> 07:42.374
I think it just means that
we have to complete our task.

07:42.462 --> 07:44.768
Fix Jake's bike,
and then the spell
will break by itself.

07:44.855 --> 07:46.117
Seems pretty
straightforward.

07:46.204 --> 07:47.162
Don't jinx it.

07:49.730 --> 07:52.602
♪♪

08:13.536 --> 08:15.320
Okay.
Eat on three.

08:15.407 --> 08:16.713
One, two--

08:18.541 --> 08:19.847
Hm. Not bad.

08:19.934 --> 08:22.502
I think we added
too much-- Whoa.

08:26.767 --> 08:28.812
We all saw that,
right?

08:28.899 --> 08:30.814
Yeah.
What were those wires?

08:30.901 --> 08:33.337
They were probably connectors
to the cold control thermostat.

08:33.424 --> 08:34.861
We might want to open up
the fridge liner,

08:34.948 --> 08:36.690
and swap out the ends
with copper tips.

08:36.777 --> 08:40.128
I have no idea how,
but I totally
understood that.

08:40.215 --> 08:43.434
We gonna need
an 18 volt power drill
with a 3/8ths bit.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.046
[chuckling]

08:47.048 --> 08:48.397
Why'd you guys call me?

08:48.484 --> 08:50.486
Because we really
need you to see this.

09:02.367 --> 09:04.935
Say hello to Jake's
actually deluxe

09:05.022 --> 09:06.676
deluxe food bike.

09:06.763 --> 09:09.287
This is amazing.

09:09.374 --> 09:10.898
Let me guess.
Magic?

09:10.985 --> 09:13.204
Just to see
what was broken.

09:13.291 --> 09:14.597
But we fixed it
ourselves.

09:14.684 --> 09:16.033
We wanted to
help you out.

09:16.120 --> 09:18.993
You've been working
really hard.

09:19.080 --> 09:20.516
It does look
a lot nicer.

09:20.603 --> 09:22.779
And check this out.

09:24.259 --> 09:27.654
Whoa.
That's awesome.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.917
I can't believe you guys
did this for me.

09:30.004 --> 09:31.962
You're the greatest.
Really.

09:32.049 --> 09:33.834
Thanks so much.

09:33.921 --> 09:35.009
I gotta run.

09:35.096 --> 09:36.793
Jake is back in business.

09:42.407 --> 09:44.061
[chuckles]
Bye.

09:46.803 --> 09:49.197
- I'm exhausted.
- Me, too.

09:49.284 --> 09:51.068
Who knew fixing things
was such a workout?

09:51.155 --> 09:53.767
It took all day.
Summer fun tomorrow?

09:53.854 --> 09:56.291
Let's just do it
before it's our
winter of fun.

10:14.962 --> 10:16.398
As long as I'm up here.

10:27.583 --> 10:29.324
I should do something
about that.

10:32.370 --> 10:33.589
What are you doing?

10:33.676 --> 10:35.983
These cost $200.

10:36.070 --> 10:38.463
And looked 200 years old
with all those holes.

10:38.550 --> 10:40.857
They're supposed to.
It's called fashion.

10:40.944 --> 10:43.120
I saw them in the laundry
and I just had to fix them,

10:43.207 --> 10:45.296
because...

10:45.383 --> 10:46.428
I just had to.

10:46.515 --> 10:48.299
You would.

11:09.625 --> 11:10.931
Oh, no.

11:15.675 --> 11:17.677
I was up all night
grouting the shower.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.896
I only slept two hours,
and when I did,

11:19.983 --> 11:22.420
I dreamt I was repairing
all the school's lockers.

11:22.507 --> 11:24.292
I thought that the magic
was supposed to break

11:24.379 --> 11:27.208
once we fixed
Jake's business.

11:27.295 --> 11:28.818
It doesn't look
fixed to me.

11:28.905 --> 11:31.255
Jake, why aren't you at
the office complex?

11:31.342 --> 11:33.040
What happened with
the property manager?

11:33.127 --> 11:34.432
Remember all those
terrible things

11:34.519 --> 11:36.521
Mama P said at
the Pluot Festival?

11:36.608 --> 11:39.220
So does everyone else,
especially Jess Montel.

11:39.307 --> 11:40.830
Once she realized
I work for Mama P,

11:40.917 --> 11:42.440
I couldn't get past
security.

11:42.527 --> 11:44.355
Even when I offered them
free samples

11:44.442 --> 11:45.835
of my PB&amp;J bites.

11:45.922 --> 11:48.838
Ooh, what'd you do with
the free samples?

11:48.925 --> 11:51.711
I mean,
I'm so sorry.

11:51.798 --> 11:52.929
That's what happens
when your boss is

11:53.016 --> 11:54.975
the most hated woman
in town.

11:55.062 --> 11:56.585
I'm sorry to waste
all your hard work.

12:06.203 --> 12:07.988
Great.

12:08.075 --> 12:11.643
Jake's business
is being ruined by
Mama P's reputation.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.645
How are we
supposed to fix that?

12:13.733 --> 12:15.343
We can't.

12:15.430 --> 12:17.040
We need
a counter-spell.

12:18.346 --> 12:21.610
Ugh!
Worst magic ever.

12:21.697 --> 12:23.307
I find it
kind of calming.

12:25.222 --> 12:27.050
I think I found
something.

12:27.137 --> 12:29.096
"Chill Out Chalupas."

12:29.183 --> 12:31.011
It should stop our
compulsive focus on--

12:41.064 --> 12:42.718
What are you doing?

12:42.805 --> 12:44.676
I think I'm trying to
fix the book.

12:47.854 --> 12:48.811
No way.

12:51.205 --> 12:52.815
8-5-2-9.

12:54.425 --> 12:56.297
What do you think
it means?

12:56.384 --> 12:57.298
I don't know but--

12:59.822 --> 13:01.693
Oh, the bean bag is ripping,
I need to fix it.

13:01.781 --> 13:02.738
- No.
- Right.

13:02.825 --> 13:04.784
Counter-spell first.

13:04.871 --> 13:08.265
Okay,
the recipe says we need
cedronian paprika.

13:08.352 --> 13:11.921
We don't have any.
We're gonna have to go
to Mama P's.

13:12.008 --> 13:14.881
[locks rattling]

13:14.968 --> 13:16.708
So you're under
a fixer spell?

13:16.796 --> 13:17.884
Oh, that's a hoot.

13:21.713 --> 13:25.413
[sighs]
Cedronian paprika,
cedronian paprika--

13:25.500 --> 13:26.980
It's not here.

13:27.067 --> 13:30.722
Odd. I could have sworn
I had some.

13:30.810 --> 13:33.377
It's been so long since
I've been in my pantry,

13:33.464 --> 13:34.465
I guess I forgot.

13:34.552 --> 13:36.293
What are we gonna do?

13:36.380 --> 13:37.947
There's no way
to break this.

13:41.559 --> 13:43.474
We can't fix
Jake's business

13:43.561 --> 13:44.911
until we fix
your reputation.

13:44.998 --> 13:47.696
Hm, that seems to be
the case.

13:47.783 --> 13:50.438
But as long as you're on
this fixing kick,

13:50.525 --> 13:52.527
why not take a look
at that leaky faucet.

14:03.103 --> 14:05.975
Oh, that's sneaky.

14:27.344 --> 14:30.260
[sighs]
Okay, traveler.

14:30.347 --> 14:31.914
Where are you?

14:36.919 --> 14:38.703
[sighs]
It's not working.

14:38.790 --> 14:39.835
[gasping]

14:45.536 --> 14:47.451
[panting]

14:49.932 --> 14:51.455
[hammering]

14:54.197 --> 14:56.069
[sanding]

14:58.027 --> 15:00.812
Uh, what are
you guys doing?

15:00.900 --> 15:02.640
Helping Mama P
against our wills.

15:02.727 --> 15:04.512
Hannah:
It's the downside
to the magic.

15:04.599 --> 15:06.209
We're trying to fix
your business,

15:06.296 --> 15:08.211
but it's affected by
her reputation.

15:09.647 --> 15:10.735
Don't remind me.

15:10.822 --> 15:12.650
They're in quite
the pickle.

15:12.737 --> 15:13.913
Nice of them to
help you out, though.

15:15.523 --> 15:16.480
We need a plan.

15:16.567 --> 15:18.395
No one trusts
Mama P.

15:18.482 --> 15:20.658
They're not coming in here
without a serious re-branding.

15:20.745 --> 15:22.747
Then let's do just that.

15:22.834 --> 15:25.402
New signs, new menu,
it'll be a grand re-opening.

15:25.489 --> 15:26.664
I like the sound of that.

15:28.753 --> 15:31.713
We can redecorate.
Balloons, streamers,
a banner.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.976
I have been thinking about
bringing in some live music.

15:34.063 --> 15:36.196
But nobody's
going to come.

15:36.283 --> 15:37.632
Saffron Falls
can hold a grudge.

15:37.719 --> 15:39.286
So I've noticed.

15:39.373 --> 15:41.766
It's true.
We need something to
draw people in.

15:41.853 --> 15:43.812
Easy.
Give out free food.

15:43.899 --> 15:45.727
Who can resist
free food?

15:45.814 --> 15:47.511
Good idea,
but we also need to

15:47.598 --> 15:49.949
make sure
that they come back,
so...

15:50.036 --> 15:53.300
we need you
to apologize.
To everyone.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.258
I've got nothing to
apologize for.

15:55.345 --> 15:56.303
Seriously?

15:56.390 --> 15:58.435
I said a few
nasty things.

15:58.522 --> 16:01.134
But it's not my fault
this town is full of
crybabies.

16:01.221 --> 16:03.745
Typical.
Do you want your
reputation back,

16:03.832 --> 16:05.747
or is your pride gonna
put us both out of a job?

16:07.009 --> 16:09.838
Fine.
I'll do it.

16:09.925 --> 16:11.535
Great.

16:11.622 --> 16:13.102
Anything else?

16:13.189 --> 16:15.844
Because I think I've got
the live music covered.

16:15.931 --> 16:17.150
No.

16:17.237 --> 16:19.587
The whole town would
come to see you play.

16:19.674 --> 16:22.024
We need everyone we can get
for Mama P's apology.

16:22.111 --> 16:24.331
Help Ida?
I'd rather rot.

16:25.549 --> 16:27.203
It wouldn't
just be for her.

16:27.290 --> 16:29.814
Without your help,
we're stuck fixing things
forever.

16:29.901 --> 16:32.513
This could be
your second chance.

16:32.600 --> 16:35.081
I haven't seen a stage
in decades.

16:35.168 --> 16:36.778
Stop trying to fix me.

16:36.865 --> 16:40.434
There's nothing to fix.
Trust me.

16:40.521 --> 16:41.826
The only thing
wrong with you is

16:41.913 --> 16:43.698
you've lost
your confidence.

16:43.785 --> 16:45.830
I have plenty
of confidence.

16:45.917 --> 16:48.311
That's not what I see.

16:48.398 --> 16:51.532
You should
believe in yourself,
Miss Silvers.

16:51.619 --> 16:52.576
I do.

17:01.803 --> 17:03.935
Becky: It's you.
Where have you been?

17:04.022 --> 17:06.155
Rose.

17:06.242 --> 17:08.810
We need your help.
Chuck's back.

17:08.896 --> 17:10.724
Rose.

17:10.811 --> 17:14.250
I don't understand.
What does that mean?

17:14.337 --> 17:15.425
Rose.

17:15.512 --> 17:17.036
[gasping]

17:21.692 --> 17:23.781
Mama P:
Look at this crowd.

17:23.867 --> 17:25.695
The store
looks amazing.

17:25.782 --> 17:28.047
I should keep you girls
spelled all the time.

17:28.134 --> 17:30.310
You know,
you could just
say thank you.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.225
Remember, Mama P,
this is only gonna work

17:32.312 --> 17:33.704
if you tell everyone
you're sorry.

17:33.791 --> 17:35.619
I know how to apologize.

17:35.706 --> 17:37.099
Sorry.

17:37.186 --> 17:39.841
They might be expecting
a little more than that.

17:42.496 --> 17:46.413
Gina. Gracing us
with your talent?

17:46.500 --> 17:48.502
I am not here
for you, Ida.

17:52.462 --> 17:54.421
So?
Are you gonna play?

17:54.508 --> 17:56.640
I'll have to
shake off some rust,

17:56.727 --> 18:00.818
but you believed in me
so maybe my time hasn't
passed quite yet.

18:02.646 --> 18:05.345
Here,
let me show you the piano
Mr. Jensen brought you.

18:34.983 --> 18:38.421
♪♪[Chopin Nocturne Op. 9,
No. 1 in B flat minor]

18:55.177 --> 18:58.049
Miss Silvers
is incredible.

18:58.137 --> 18:59.616
I knew she
had it in her.

18:59.703 --> 19:01.662
And she actually
looks happy.

19:03.142 --> 19:06.232
♪♪

19:08.234 --> 19:10.236
We've got a problem.

19:10.323 --> 19:11.237
Chuck.

19:12.325 --> 19:13.413
What do we do now?

19:13.500 --> 19:14.718
I've got this.

19:20.246 --> 19:21.508
What are you doing here?

19:21.595 --> 19:23.553
A guy can't listen to
a little music?

19:23.640 --> 19:24.989
You're up to something.

19:25.076 --> 19:26.774
You think so?

19:26.861 --> 19:28.079
You need to stop
looking for trouble.

19:28.167 --> 19:29.255
Or else you'll--

19:33.346 --> 19:36.566
You've been hurt.

19:36.653 --> 19:38.481
But you can be fixed.

19:40.004 --> 19:42.050
The only thing that hurts
is my arm.

19:42.137 --> 19:43.312
The way you're
grabbin' it.

19:43.399 --> 19:45.923
[applause]

19:51.233 --> 19:52.626
You're as good as
I remember.

19:57.021 --> 20:00.024
Good evening,
everyone.

20:00.111 --> 20:02.810
Hope you're enjoying
my free food.

20:02.897 --> 20:04.812
I know why you're here,

20:04.899 --> 20:07.815
so let's get this over with.

20:07.902 --> 20:08.990
I'm sorry.

20:10.948 --> 20:12.428
Pluots are a fine fruit.

20:13.864 --> 20:17.128
[sighs]
Saffron Falls
is a good town,

20:17.216 --> 20:20.697
and everyone here is...

20:20.784 --> 20:21.742
a person.

20:21.829 --> 20:23.961
[chatter]

20:25.659 --> 20:27.356
Dine and dash.
That's nice.

20:27.443 --> 20:28.401
This isn't going
very well.

20:28.488 --> 20:29.706
What do you want?

20:29.793 --> 20:32.535
For me to say everyone here
is so pleasant

20:32.622 --> 20:36.104
that I didn't wake up
every morning miserable?

20:36.191 --> 20:37.932
Because the truth is--

20:41.109 --> 20:42.632
I am sorry.

20:44.286 --> 20:48.508
I was selfish.
I was arrogant.

20:48.595 --> 20:49.770
And I hurt you.

20:53.077 --> 20:56.211
You might not ever
be able to forgive me,
but--

20:58.213 --> 21:00.171
I hope you can give me
a second chance.

21:01.347 --> 21:03.871
[applause]

21:08.789 --> 21:10.007
How do I order
a batch of these

21:10.094 --> 21:11.226
peanut butter
and jelly treats?

21:11.313 --> 21:13.446
Whoa.
You're Jess Montel.

21:13.533 --> 21:14.795
Uh, I can get you
a box of bites.

21:14.882 --> 21:16.144
They're my
original recipe.

21:16.231 --> 21:17.319
You're the kid
that was trying to

21:17.406 --> 21:18.668
sell food
outside my office.

21:18.755 --> 21:19.974
Yeah, and I know
you didn't--

21:20.061 --> 21:21.192
I think that's
a great idea.

21:21.280 --> 21:23.543
Be there tomorrow
12:30 sharp.

21:23.630 --> 21:26.285
And, uh, have plenty
of these on hand.

21:26.372 --> 21:27.547
See you then.

21:30.941 --> 21:33.466
Wow, Mama P.
I didn't think
you had it in you.

21:33.553 --> 21:35.903
Well, I was a bit
surprised myself.

21:35.990 --> 21:37.905
While I have you,

21:37.992 --> 21:41.822
the espresso machine
has been on the fritz
since yesterday.

21:45.129 --> 21:47.697
Actually, it seems
we just fixed our problem.

21:47.784 --> 21:50.265
So I guess you're
on your own.

21:53.747 --> 21:55.270
[crickets chirping]

21:56.706 --> 21:59.013
What did the traveler
say, Grandma?

21:59.100 --> 22:00.449
Nothing.

22:00.536 --> 22:02.364
I only saw her
in a dream.

22:02.451 --> 22:05.149
That's weird.
We saw her in
our dream, too.

22:05.236 --> 22:06.586
- All of you?
- Yeah.

22:06.673 --> 22:09.197
She told us that
we had to protect
the book.

22:09.284 --> 22:11.982
Strange.

22:12.069 --> 22:14.071
With me, she--

22:14.158 --> 22:16.291
She just looked sick.

22:16.378 --> 22:20.643
And she kept saying
this one word over
and over again. Rose.

22:20.730 --> 22:24.517
Really? That's it?
She didn't say anything else?

22:24.604 --> 22:26.127
You don't believe me.

22:26.214 --> 22:28.956
I didn't say that,
I was--

22:29.043 --> 22:32.655
Just hoping.

22:32.742 --> 22:33.787
What do you think
rose means?

22:33.874 --> 22:36.485
I don't know.

22:36.572 --> 22:39.009
But the traveler
may not be able to help us.

22:41.882 --> 22:44.754
♪♪

22:51.195 --> 22:54.721
It was nice to have
people in here again.

22:54.808 --> 22:56.853
Maybe next time
they'll actually pay.

22:56.940 --> 22:59.073
Just put my PB&amp;J bites
on the menu.

22:59.160 --> 23:00.466
They were a hit.

23:01.815 --> 23:04.557
I can finish
closing up, Jake.

23:04.644 --> 23:06.602
You've already done
more than enough today.

23:06.689 --> 23:07.995
Great. Thanks.

23:09.692 --> 23:13.348
Hey, uh, Mama P.
Thanks.

23:13.435 --> 23:14.523
For saying what you said
up there.

23:14.610 --> 23:17.396
Yes, well, I meant it.

23:18.962 --> 23:20.616
I could tell.

23:20.703 --> 23:21.922
Goodnight, Mama P.

23:22.009 --> 23:23.445
Goodnight, Jake.

23:26.143 --> 23:27.275
[bell jingles]

23:33.934 --> 23:36.806
♪♪

23:50.994 --> 23:54.433
Hannah:
Cedronian paprika,
cedronian paprika--

23:57.653 --> 23:59.089
It's not here.

23:59.176 --> 24:00.177
Well, that's odd.

24:01.222 --> 24:04.138
♪♪

